    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, mash the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix thoroughly</p><p>Line a baking tray with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong> and add 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12] </span>spoonfuls of <strong>potato mix </strong>to the tray</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, pat each spoonful of <strong>potato mix</strong> down and put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until golden – these are your <strong>potato cakes</strong></p>",
